  <prompt>
    <goal>Implement three test execution modes for playbooks: Mock (simulated), Quick (temp storage), Production (real data).</goal>

    <context>
      Test modes allow users to validate playbooks before production use:
      - Mock: Generate sample data, no external calls
      - Quick: Upload test document to temp container, execute once
      - Production: Execute against real data with full observability
    </context>

    <constraints>
      - Use existing PlaybookOrchestrationService for execution
      - Mock mode must not make any external calls
      - Quick mode must use playbook-test-documents container
      - Production mode requires explicit user confirmation
    </constraints>
  </prompt>

